WEBVTT

00:00.701 --> 00:01.702
LEA: Previously on
The Good Doctor...

00:03.504 --> 00:07.375
I'm producing a reality
wedding series for Hulu
about atypical couples.

00:07.508 --> 00:09.610
JORDAN: You are not
a reality show person.

00:09.743 --> 00:11.445
Have you guys
thought any more
about doing my show?

00:13.314 --> 00:16.450
There are people who need
to know you exist, Shaun.

00:16.584 --> 00:20.054
When I was younger,
I would have liked
to see a TV show

00:20.188 --> 00:23.624
about a man like me
lucky enough to marry
a woman like you.

00:23.757 --> 00:27.461
We are going to be
reality show people.

00:27.595 --> 00:29.997
SOPHIE: You and Lea
and your relationship,

00:30.131 --> 00:32.200
that is what
will give hope.

00:32.333 --> 00:33.634
Is it time
for the surprise?

00:35.103 --> 00:36.970
WOMAN: Congratulations,
Shaun and Lea.

00:37.105 --> 00:39.039
(CHEERING)

00:39.173 --> 00:42.476
****

00:46.947 --> 00:49.016
CLAIRE: Ah,
the first time
I met Shaun.

00:49.150 --> 00:55.055
Um, he was wet and cold

00:55.189 --> 00:57.491
and a bit like, um...

00:58.792 --> 01:02.196
Like, I remember thinking
he was like a lost puppy.

01:02.330 --> 01:04.865
So adorable,
but so helpless,

01:04.998 --> 01:09.837
and definitely not a likely
source of medical insight.

01:09.970 --> 01:13.241
Um, but he was the only one

01:13.374 --> 01:15.509
who knew how to save
that little boy's life.

01:15.643 --> 01:17.511
SHAUN: Pancakes are ready.

01:18.512 --> 01:21.515
****

01:21.649 --> 01:24.518
I'm supposed to pretend
you aren't here.

01:24.652 --> 01:26.554
But you are also welcome
to my pancakes.

01:27.855 --> 01:29.423
Even though
I really do not like

01:29.557 --> 01:31.692
all of you being
in my apartment.

01:31.825 --> 01:34.928
There are
11 chocolate chips
in each pancake.

01:35.062 --> 01:37.064
CLAIRE: So much to do
in just two days.

01:37.198 --> 01:39.600
That is why Sophie
is the genius.

01:39.733 --> 01:41.935
Each book
is a different theme.

01:42.069 --> 01:44.272
We pick one and all
the decisions are made.

01:44.405 --> 01:47.208
Flowers, decor,
food, music.

01:47.341 --> 01:48.409
I actually feel
kinda great.

01:49.577 --> 01:51.479
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

01:51.612 --> 01:53.247
Oh. Someone
is at the door.

01:56.217 --> 01:58.452
Oh. I heard there
would be pancakes

01:58.586 --> 02:01.755
and a chance
to see my friend!

02:01.889 --> 02:04.158
(BOTH LAUGH)
Hi.

02:04.292 --> 02:06.327
Aw.
I'm so glad you're here.

02:06.460 --> 02:08.562
Oh, I wouldn't have skipped
the wedding of the century.

02:08.696 --> 02:11.465
And maybe I missed you
a bit too.

02:11.599 --> 02:14.268
As much as you miss
the chai lattes
from Josefa Joe's?

02:14.402 --> 02:15.536
(GASPS) Almost.

02:15.669 --> 02:16.904
Hmm?
Thank you.

02:17.037 --> 02:18.272
(CHUCKLES)

02:18.406 --> 02:19.707
You must be very proud
of Dr. Browne,

02:19.840 --> 02:21.575
soon to be following
in your footsteps.

02:21.709 --> 02:24.111
Oh, uh, they offered me

02:24.245 --> 02:25.779
chief of surgery in Guatemala.

02:25.913 --> 02:27.748
Wow, congratulations.

02:27.881 --> 02:29.683
I haven't
decided yet, but...

02:29.817 --> 02:31.385
Well, either way,
I'm, yeah, very proud.

02:31.519 --> 02:32.820
(CHUCKLES)

02:32.953 --> 02:35.456
Fifty-two hours
and counting
till wedded bliss.

02:35.589 --> 02:37.157
Let's move.

02:37.291 --> 02:39.126
Okay, the limo-bus
is outside.

02:39.260 --> 02:40.394
Time for you
to get manicured,

02:40.528 --> 02:43.364
massaged, and fitted
for your dream dress.

02:43.497 --> 02:45.165
(GASPS) A limo-bus?

02:45.299 --> 02:46.334
(SQUEALS)

02:46.467 --> 02:49.937
****

02:50.070 --> 02:53.006
Goodbye,
my soon-to-be husband.

02:53.140 --> 02:54.675
****

02:55.509 --> 02:56.510
Bye, have fun.

02:56.644 --> 02:57.911
Ah, Lucho just landed.
Gotta get ready.

02:58.045 --> 02:59.012
Okay.

02:59.146 --> 03:01.982
Does Claire
have a boyfriend?

03:02.115 --> 03:04.318
Sophie will need to know
if he likes chicken or beef
or veg...

03:04.452 --> 03:06.420
Not a boyfriend.
A patient.

03:07.721 --> 03:08.956
(EXHALES)

03:09.089 --> 03:10.824
Sophie offered me
a "plus one,"

03:10.958 --> 03:12.493
and I decided to go for it.

03:12.626 --> 03:14.562
Apparently I have
some leverage.

03:14.695 --> 03:16.297
If you're gonna be
chief of surgery,

03:16.430 --> 03:18.632
you'll have
a lot of it.

03:18.766 --> 03:20.368
Do you think
I could cut it
as chief?

03:20.501 --> 03:21.502
Sure.

03:21.635 --> 03:24.171
Oh, my gosh!
It's so good
to see you.

03:24.305 --> 03:25.539
Buenos dias.

03:25.673 --> 03:27.174
Buenos dias y gracias,
Alyssa.

03:27.308 --> 03:28.509
Doctora Claire!

03:28.642 --> 03:29.910
Hola, Lucho!

03:30.043 --> 03:31.211
Como estuvo tu vuelo?

03:31.345 --> 03:33.547
I had pizza
and chocolate milk,

03:33.681 --> 03:37.050
and I flew over the, uh,
Grand Canyon and Fresno.

03:37.184 --> 03:38.852
Mm.
You got the royal tour.

03:38.986 --> 03:42.390
These are your friends
who are going
to save my life?

03:42.523 --> 03:44.191
Si. Y si.

03:44.325 --> 03:48.028
Doctora Claire nos
dijo que tienes tumores
en los rinones.

03:48.161 --> 03:50.130
Si. Y si.

03:50.264 --> 03:52.366
****

03:55.969 --> 03:56.937
Okay.

03:57.070 --> 03:58.672
****

04:01.975 --> 04:03.377
Oh.

04:03.511 --> 04:05.746
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

04:13.521 --> 04:16.223
(ULTRASOUND MACHINE WARBLING)

04:16.357 --> 04:17.858
These tumors have been

04:17.991 --> 04:19.460
growing for many years.

04:19.593 --> 04:21.061
Lucho is from
a small village

04:21.194 --> 04:23.297
with very limited
access to medical care.

04:23.431 --> 04:25.666
I will play futbol again?

04:25.799 --> 04:27.200
Ahora que viajaste
a Estados Unidos,

04:27.335 --> 04:28.369
podemos ayudarte.

04:29.537 --> 04:30.438
Your Spanish is impressive.

04:30.571 --> 04:32.239
Turns out,
immersion works.

04:32.373 --> 04:34.174
You did mispronounce

04:34.308 --> 04:35.643
via-chah-stay.

04:35.776 --> 04:37.177
(GIGGLES)
Via-hah-stay.
(LAUGHTER)

04:37.311 --> 04:39.112
Okay. (CHUCKLES)

04:39.246 --> 04:41.181
Your English
is impressive, too.

04:42.383 --> 04:43.717
I teach Spanish.

04:43.851 --> 04:45.218
Doctora Claire teach English.

04:45.353 --> 04:46.987
He taught me
how to watch futbol.

04:48.255 --> 04:49.289
How you say marcando?

04:49.423 --> 04:50.491
Scoring.

04:50.624 --> 04:51.659
El portero?

04:51.792 --> 04:53.260
The goalkeeper.
(GIGGLES)

04:53.394 --> 04:55.396
El arbitro es un culo?

04:56.930 --> 04:59.266
The referee
is a rectum.

04:59.400 --> 05:01.435
(LAUGHS)

05:01.569 --> 05:02.503
(GASPS) Ah.

05:02.636 --> 05:05.506
****

05:05.639 --> 05:07.307
What did his imaging show?

05:07.441 --> 05:09.309
Guatemala, remember?

05:09.443 --> 05:11.078
Closest MRI
is an 11-hour bus ride.

05:11.211 --> 05:13.246
(CELL PHONE BUZZES)

05:13.381 --> 05:15.282
I'll catch up with you
in radiology.

05:15.416 --> 05:16.216
Hasta luego, Lucho.

05:16.350 --> 05:18.652
****

05:23.457 --> 05:25.493
(ALARMS BEEPING)

05:25.626 --> 05:26.894
He's in V-tach.

05:27.027 --> 05:28.095
We already tried
defibrillating him twice.

05:28.228 --> 05:30.030
His heart rate
is over 180.

05:30.163 --> 05:31.765
(BEEPING CONTINUES)

05:33.667 --> 05:35.769
I'm giving him
12 milligrams adenosine.

05:35.903 --> 05:38.038
****

05:38.171 --> 05:39.473
(ALARMS STOP)

05:39.607 --> 05:40.674
Rhythm's normalizing.

05:40.808 --> 05:42.309
His rhythm had
a retrograde P wave.

05:42.443 --> 05:44.277
The beta blockers
were working perfectly
the last 48 hours.

05:44.412 --> 05:45.145
What happened?

05:46.947 --> 05:48.148
Patient didn't get them
last night.

05:48.281 --> 05:49.049
Why not?

05:50.918 --> 05:52.386
Who was covering
the floor?

05:54.422 --> 05:55.155
Villanueva.

05:57.825 --> 05:59.192
Let me know when
her shift starts.

06:01.328 --> 06:02.329
(ELEVATOR DINGS)

06:02.463 --> 06:03.997
Hey.

06:04.131 --> 06:05.833
Have you seen
Claire today?

06:05.966 --> 06:07.901
She's here with her
ridiculously adorable patient

06:08.035 --> 06:09.002
from Guatemala.

06:09.136 --> 06:10.370
Kidney tumors, right?
Mm-hmm.

06:10.504 --> 06:11.839
Not yet.
I've been slammed.

06:11.972 --> 06:13.641
Then you'll be glad to scratch
getting Shaun and Lea

06:13.774 --> 06:15.208
a wedding present
off your to-do list.

06:15.342 --> 06:16.977
What did "we" get them?

06:17.110 --> 06:19.379
A bread maker.
Do they even eat bread?

06:19.513 --> 06:20.581
Everyone eats bread.

06:20.714 --> 06:22.215
And the correct
response is,

06:22.349 --> 06:24.485
"Thanks for
taking care of that.
I really appreciate it."

06:28.456 --> 06:31.224
(SQUEALS) So happy
you're playing hooky
with me.

06:31.358 --> 06:33.894
Girl, I'd take
a week off for this.

06:34.027 --> 06:35.195
This is bigger than
my apartment.

06:35.328 --> 06:36.597
(UP-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

06:36.730 --> 06:38.098
Whoo!

06:38.231 --> 06:40.100
Okay, come on.
You have to help me
choose my theme.

06:40.233 --> 06:41.835
I'm so not Rustic.

06:42.703 --> 06:44.572
Traditional feels stuffy.

06:44.705 --> 06:46.540
Glam could be fun.

06:46.674 --> 06:47.841
Too over-the-top.

06:49.309 --> 06:50.511
Tropical?

06:50.644 --> 06:52.546
I am definitely not wearing
a coconut shell bra.

06:52.680 --> 06:54.347
As I said, Tropical,
hard pass.

06:54.482 --> 06:55.616
What about Retro?

06:55.749 --> 06:58.018
You would kill
in a '50s dress,

06:58.151 --> 07:00.320
and I can see
Shaun going Buddy Holly.

07:00.454 --> 07:02.155
Too Happy Days.

07:02.289 --> 07:06.026
I'm thinking something
more...sophisticated.

07:06.159 --> 07:07.595
Then Nautical is out.

07:07.728 --> 07:10.363
And Celestial,
whatever that is,
just, no.

07:10.498 --> 07:13.767
****

07:13.901 --> 07:15.569
Harry Potter?

07:15.703 --> 07:17.738
Okay, well, one day...

07:17.871 --> 07:19.072
(LEA LAUGHS)

07:19.206 --> 07:20.508
...someone is gonna choose
Harry Potter.

07:22.109 --> 07:23.544
And it will be glorious.

07:25.378 --> 07:26.947
(GASPS) What about this one?

07:27.080 --> 07:30.050
Ooh. Upscale Elegance.

07:30.183 --> 07:32.052
I think I kinda love it.

07:32.185 --> 07:36.590
Satin, crystals, candles,
and flowers everywhere.

07:36.724 --> 07:39.259
It's more beautiful
than I could have dreamed.

07:39.392 --> 07:41.094
Okay, now all you two
have to do

07:41.228 --> 07:43.964
is choose between brut
and extra brut

07:44.097 --> 07:45.566
before we get
to the spa.

07:47.535 --> 07:50.103
Okay. (SQUEALS)

07:50.237 --> 07:52.906
(MRI MACHINE WHIRRING)

07:58.211 --> 07:59.980
How many ring options
did Sophie give you?

08:00.113 --> 08:01.081
Ninety-four.

08:01.214 --> 08:03.551
But they are all
very expensive.

08:03.684 --> 08:05.686
Lea would rather have
a new laptop.

08:05.819 --> 08:07.755
(CHUCKLES)
You sure about that?

08:07.888 --> 08:10.891
An eternal symbol
of the unbreakable
bond of love

08:11.024 --> 08:12.325
versus
a faster processor?

08:13.961 --> 08:15.796
(DOOR OPENS, CLOSES)

08:15.929 --> 08:16.930
Anything?

08:17.064 --> 08:18.431
Imaging coming up now.

08:20.200 --> 08:23.203
Do you really think
I would make a good
chief of surgery?

08:23.336 --> 08:25.573
Dr. Lim often leaves
before I do,

08:25.706 --> 08:26.974
so it can't be
that hard a job.

08:28.275 --> 08:30.443
Maybe that's me
making it look easy.

08:30.578 --> 08:31.511
Maybe.

08:31.645 --> 08:32.946
I think you'd be great.

08:34.147 --> 08:34.948
But...

08:35.649 --> 08:37.017
But nothing.

08:38.051 --> 08:40.020
Come on.
You hesitated earlier.

08:41.154 --> 08:42.455
I want to know
what you really think.

08:42.590 --> 08:43.791
Your opinion
matters to me.

08:48.295 --> 08:50.664
Some days can be
very challenging

08:50.798 --> 08:54.334
and you have to be prepared
to put your emotions aside.

08:56.436 --> 08:57.971
Right, so you don't think
that I can do that?

09:00.307 --> 09:02.676
You are the kindest,
most caring...

09:02.810 --> 09:03.777
Oh, come on.

09:03.911 --> 09:05.545
...and empathetic
person I know.

09:05.679 --> 09:07.080
It's why I miss
having you here

09:07.214 --> 09:08.048
so, so much.

09:09.482 --> 09:12.152
But you may find,
running a department,

09:12.285 --> 09:15.355
despite the short hours,
trickier than you think.

09:16.957 --> 09:18.659
Sometimes you have to be
a real hard-ass.

09:21.629 --> 09:23.764
Oh, this ring
is perfect.

09:25.032 --> 09:27.567
Lea can sell it
and get two laptops.

09:27.701 --> 09:29.637
(COMPUTER CHIRPS)

09:29.770 --> 09:30.704
There's the tumors.

09:33.006 --> 09:35.008
Oh, marked vascularity.

09:35.142 --> 09:36.810
Gonna be a high risk
of bleeding.

09:36.944 --> 09:40.013
And look at that,
left atrium.

09:40.147 --> 09:42.415
He has a tumor
in the heart too.

09:42.549 --> 09:45.886
It's small, but it will
be difficult to access.

09:46.019 --> 09:48.722
(COMPUTER WARBLES)

09:48.856 --> 09:50.523
And one in his brain.

09:51.959 --> 09:54.194
And that one is not small.

09:54.327 --> 09:56.730
****

10:02.302 --> 10:03.470
DR. ANDREWS: Rather than
bring us one case,

10:03.536 --> 10:05.405
it appears Dr. Browne
has actually brought us three.

10:06.539 --> 10:10.110
All complex,
all potentially
fatal surgeries.

10:10.243 --> 10:12.245
So, I've assembled
three surgical teams.

10:12.379 --> 10:16.249
Doctors Glassman, Browne,
and Murphy are on Team Brain.

10:16.383 --> 10:18.318
On Team Heart,
Doctors Lim and Wolke.

10:19.519 --> 10:21.254
And on Team Kidney,
Dr. Park and myself.

10:21.388 --> 10:24.024
Each of our procedures
will be enormously impacted

10:24.157 --> 10:25.258
by the other two.

10:25.392 --> 10:27.560
We need someone to oversee
the entire process.

10:27.695 --> 10:28.862
I'll do it.

10:28.996 --> 10:31.631
I was thinking of someone
a little more...experienced.

10:34.201 --> 10:35.836
You mean someone
a little more detached.

10:35.969 --> 10:37.570
I think there's
an overlap there.

10:37.705 --> 10:38.772
Not necessarily.

10:41.574 --> 10:43.443
Take it away.

10:43.576 --> 10:46.079
****

10:49.282 --> 10:52.585
We now have the bouquets,
the centerpieces,

10:52.720 --> 10:53.987
the music set list,

10:54.121 --> 10:56.589
and the menus with
the extra brut.

10:56.724 --> 10:57.858
You're amazing.

10:57.991 --> 10:59.993
Yesterday,
she was a documentarian.

11:00.127 --> 11:02.429
Today, she's a field general.

11:02.562 --> 11:04.031
Yeah. Deadlines
are my friends.

11:04.164 --> 11:05.665
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

11:05.799 --> 11:07.801
We have 48 guests confirmed
for your side,

11:07.935 --> 11:10.603
and only nine guests
confirmed for Shaun.

11:12.639 --> 11:14.474
No parents?
No extended family?

11:14.607 --> 11:17.911
Well, his father
and brother
have passed,

11:18.045 --> 11:20.013
and he doesn't
talk to his mom.

11:20.147 --> 11:22.315
Oh. That's hard.

11:23.183 --> 11:24.317
Yeah.

11:24.451 --> 11:26.353
Eh, we'll just cover it up
with seat fillers.

11:27.120 --> 11:28.355
Seat fillers?

11:28.488 --> 11:30.523
Oh, yeah.
No one will know
the difference.

11:32.159 --> 11:34.094
And we just
bumped your parents

11:34.227 --> 11:35.128
up to first class
on their flight.

11:36.163 --> 11:37.130
Seriously?

11:38.531 --> 11:40.934
Oh! They're gonna
love that.

11:41.068 --> 11:42.535
I will have a camera crew
waiting for them

11:42.669 --> 11:44.071
at the airport
when they land.

11:44.204 --> 11:47.140
And I believe, here come
the seaweed wraps.

11:47.274 --> 11:49.542
(EXHALES DEEPLY) Yes!

11:50.844 --> 11:52.312
Oh, my God.

11:52.445 --> 11:53.713
Mmm.

11:55.783 --> 11:56.784
Dissecting.

11:56.917 --> 11:58.151
(MONITOR BEEPING)

11:58.285 --> 12:00.320
Damn. Going again.

12:00.453 --> 12:01.421
(CLICK, BEEPING STOPS)

12:05.192 --> 12:07.160
Have you decided
on Shaun and Lea's
wedding present?

12:09.196 --> 12:11.064
You know how
I love a good cab,

12:11.198 --> 12:13.801
so I'm giving them
a weekend in Napa.

12:13.934 --> 12:16.436
Yeah.
It's a working vineyard
and dairy farm,

12:16.569 --> 12:19.239
so Lea drinks wine,
Shaun drinks one percent.

12:19.372 --> 12:20.173
You?

12:21.875 --> 12:22.843
Uh, a bread maker.

12:24.377 --> 12:25.745
Morgan chose it.

12:25.879 --> 12:27.747
Mm. I didn't know
they were into bread.

12:29.116 --> 12:30.083
I'm sure they'll love it.

12:30.217 --> 12:31.584
(DOOR OPENS)

12:31.718 --> 12:33.120
How's Team Kidney?

12:33.253 --> 12:35.322
(MACHINE BEEPING)
(SIGHS)

12:35.455 --> 12:36.756
There's just too many
tortuous vessels.

12:36.890 --> 12:38.058
(CLICK, BEEPING STOPS)

12:38.191 --> 12:39.692
We're never gonna do this
without excessive bleeding.

12:39.827 --> 12:41.862
Right. So, what else
do we have?

12:43.730 --> 12:46.299
Removing the kidney
is the safest option.

12:46.433 --> 12:48.368
Putting him on dialysis
for the rest of his life?

12:48.501 --> 12:50.003
It may be our only option.

12:50.137 --> 12:52.172
Dialysis in Guatemala...

12:52.305 --> 12:53.874
Lucho would be
institutionalized.

12:55.542 --> 12:57.410
(SIGHS) You need to come up
with a better plan.

13:01.281 --> 13:02.615
I like going through
the posterior wall.

13:02.749 --> 13:04.584
It gives us
the best access
to the tumor.

13:04.717 --> 13:06.386
We'd be cutting through
a massive amount of tissue.

13:06.519 --> 13:08.188
Wouldn't that seriously
weaken his heart muscle?

13:08.321 --> 13:09.823
Not as much
as the tumor will.

13:09.957 --> 13:11.658
Hey. Making any progress?

13:12.425 --> 13:13.961
Uh, you tell me.

13:14.094 --> 13:16.063
Hmm. It'll decrease
his cardiac output.

13:16.196 --> 13:18.065
Not as much
as the tumor will.

13:18.198 --> 13:20.133
It's the same surgical plan
that I came up with.

13:20.267 --> 13:22.302
Which is why
I've looked into
a non-surgical plan.

13:22.435 --> 13:24.237
M.T.O.R. inhibitors.

13:24.371 --> 13:26.073
Proven effective
at shrinking small tumors

13:26.206 --> 13:27.507
like the one
in Lucho's heart.

13:27.640 --> 13:28.942
Those meds
take months to work.

13:29.076 --> 13:30.443
Months that
Lucho will have

13:30.577 --> 13:32.079
because the heart surgery
won't have killed him.

13:32.212 --> 13:34.514
His heart will still
be stressed during
the other surgeries.

13:34.647 --> 13:36.283
He could have
a cardiac arrest
on the table.

13:36.416 --> 13:38.151
Which is why we'll have
a non-surgical team,

13:38.285 --> 13:41.354
Morgan and Asher, in the O.R.
watching for any arrhythmias.

13:41.488 --> 13:43.356
(CELL PHONE BUZZES)

13:43.490 --> 13:45.125
What about Dr. Lim?

13:45.258 --> 13:46.759
She's been promoted
to Team Brain.

13:46.894 --> 13:49.162
Well, I hope it comes
with a raise.

13:52.966 --> 13:54.334
I could tell you
everything that
was happening

13:54.467 --> 13:55.668
with my boyfriend
last night,

13:55.802 --> 13:58.505
but I know you don't
want to hear excuses.

14:00.407 --> 14:02.142
I'm sympathetic
that things
are bad at home,

14:02.275 --> 14:05.278
but a patient
could have died.

14:07.147 --> 14:08.681
I understand
if you need to fire me.

14:08.815 --> 14:11.518
Depriving you of income
isn't gonna help anything.

14:11.651 --> 14:13.653
But I am gonna put you
on administrative duties.

14:14.955 --> 14:17.757
Thank you, Dr. Lim.
I...

14:17.891 --> 14:18.959
Dalisay.

14:24.497 --> 14:25.865
You need help.

14:28.368 --> 14:30.003
This is the director
of Bayshore Women's Shelter.

14:30.137 --> 14:31.171
She's expecting
your call.

14:33.840 --> 14:35.308
It's a really
great place.

14:36.709 --> 14:37.810
It's complicated.

14:37.945 --> 14:39.546
Simplify it for me.

14:39.679 --> 14:41.681
****

14:45.218 --> 14:46.954
Two years ago,
when my mother

14:47.087 --> 14:48.321
was diagnosed
with liver cancer,

14:50.023 --> 14:51.224
it was really tough.

14:53.660 --> 14:57.664
She was a single mom.
I was her only child.

14:57.797 --> 14:58.999
And when she passed,

15:00.233 --> 15:01.334
I was alone.

15:04.271 --> 15:05.338
And that's when
I met Owen.

15:06.906 --> 15:09.409
I desperately needed someone,
and he was there for me.

15:11.611 --> 15:12.379
And now,

15:13.580 --> 15:16.349
he's...going through a lot.

15:18.051 --> 15:19.419
Not that he should
take it out on me.

15:24.691 --> 15:26.193
I know it must be hard.

15:28.795 --> 15:31.231
But I also know
it's necessary.

15:31.364 --> 15:33.366
****

15:36.369 --> 15:37.370
I'll call her.

15:38.938 --> 15:39.906
Thank you.

15:40.040 --> 15:43.043
****

15:49.582 --> 15:50.917
DR. GLASSMAN:
Look at that ventricle.

15:51.051 --> 15:52.652
It's the size of
the Lincoln Tunnel.

15:52.785 --> 15:54.754
That's where
we're gonna go in.

15:54.887 --> 15:57.757
SHAUN: It still
may not give us
full access to the tumor.

15:57.890 --> 16:00.127
To get full access,
we'd have to pop off
the skull

16:00.260 --> 16:01.894
and then burrow
through his brain.

16:02.029 --> 16:04.564
If we don't excise
all of the tumor,

16:04.697 --> 16:06.466
your surgery will be
a waste of time.

16:07.700 --> 16:08.535
Whaddya say, chief?

16:09.469 --> 16:11.271
I'm going with
Dr. Glassman.

16:11.404 --> 16:12.405
That would be
the correct answer.

16:13.273 --> 16:15.042
Okay, we're all done here.

16:16.309 --> 16:17.777
Let's close him up.

16:17.910 --> 16:19.346
Lea chose
our wedding theme.

16:19.479 --> 16:22.415
She texted me
a picture of what
I'm supposed to wear.

16:24.317 --> 16:25.485
It is called
The Gosling.

16:26.653 --> 16:28.788
CLAIRE: Ooh, very debonair.

16:28.921 --> 16:31.324
The cummerbund looks
very restrictive.

16:31.458 --> 16:32.525
CLAIRE: Oh.

16:32.659 --> 16:34.994
And that hairstyle
requires a lot of gel.

16:35.128 --> 16:37.130
I hate gel. It makes
my head feel tight.

16:37.264 --> 16:39.332
Well, then you need
to tell Lea

16:39.466 --> 16:41.000
so the two of you can
figure something else out.

16:42.135 --> 16:44.437
What do you think,
Dr. Glassman?

16:46.506 --> 16:49.609
I think if, 30 years ago,
my wife had asked me
to wear that suit,

16:49.742 --> 16:50.843
I probably wouldn't
have married her.

16:50.977 --> 16:53.080
And if Debbie
had asked me
two years ago,

16:53.213 --> 16:55.048
I probably would have
laughed her right
out of the room.

16:55.182 --> 16:57.650
So I don't have
to wear the suit?

16:57.784 --> 16:59.219
No, you don't
have to wear it.

16:59.352 --> 17:01.121
I'm just saying that...
(CHUCKLES)

17:03.123 --> 17:04.991
I don't know,
maybe my marriages
would have turned out

17:05.125 --> 17:06.093
a little bit differently

17:06.226 --> 17:08.495
if I had, you know,
worn the suit.

17:13.633 --> 17:15.968
You think Lea
wouldn't want to know
how you feel about this?

17:17.304 --> 17:18.471
It's your big day,
Shaun.

17:21.474 --> 17:22.442
(ALARMS BEEPING)

17:22.575 --> 17:24.544
BP is 201 over 123.

17:24.677 --> 17:26.579
SHAUN: He's having
a seizure!

17:30.883 --> 17:32.852
The brain tumor
is obstructing CSF flow,
causing seizures.

17:34.020 --> 17:36.356
It needs to be removed
as soon as possible.

17:36.489 --> 17:38.491
After we remove
the kidney tumors.

17:38.625 --> 17:41.228
If we go into his brain
while his kidneys
are impaired,

17:41.361 --> 17:44.063
we risk hypertension,
AML rupture, cerebral edema.

17:44.197 --> 17:45.498
If we go into his kidneys

17:45.632 --> 17:47.267
while his brain
is under pressure,

17:47.400 --> 17:49.236
then we risk
brain herniation, stroke,

17:49.369 --> 17:50.870
anoxic brain injury.

17:51.003 --> 17:52.905
Only in the case of
serious blood loss.

17:53.039 --> 17:54.407
Have you seen
his tumors?

17:54.541 --> 17:56.243
There's gonna be
some serious blood loss.

17:56.376 --> 17:57.677
Well, we think
we have a better plan.

17:57.810 --> 18:01.114
We ligate the feeding artery
before tumor resection.

18:01.248 --> 18:02.715
And, if we do
the kidney surgery first,

18:02.849 --> 18:05.152
we also
minimize the risk
of S.I.A.D.H.,

18:05.285 --> 18:07.520
which could very easily lead
to long-term heart damage.

18:07.654 --> 18:09.589
So, brain first,

18:09.722 --> 18:11.991
safer, but more likely
to leave him compromised.

18:12.125 --> 18:13.293
Kidneys first,

18:13.426 --> 18:16.529
riskier, but more likely
to lead to a full recovery.

18:20.400 --> 18:21.934
For the past four months,

18:22.068 --> 18:24.737
I have seen Lucho
stare out the window
of his hospital room

18:24.871 --> 18:26.939
watching the kids
play soccer
in the schoolyard.

18:28.908 --> 18:31.578
If there is a chance
I can get him back
out there, I'll take it.

18:31.711 --> 18:33.746
That's a lot of weight
to put on playing soccer.

18:33.880 --> 18:35.615
****

18:39.686 --> 18:42.054
We do the kidneys today,
the brain tomorrow.

18:42.189 --> 18:45.258
****

18:49.396 --> 18:51.931
Let's say
half-a-dozen oysters
per person.

18:52.064 --> 18:54.434
Oh. Olympias or Kumamotos?

18:57.069 --> 18:58.938
Uh...mix of both.

19:00.573 --> 19:01.774
Mix of both, please.

19:02.975 --> 19:04.444
(SQUEALS)

19:04.577 --> 19:06.179
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

19:07.046 --> 19:08.715
I think this is the one.

19:08.848 --> 19:10.450
JORDAN: Wow.

19:10.583 --> 19:12.084
Mm!

19:12.219 --> 19:13.653
Really?

19:13.786 --> 19:14.754
You don't love it?

19:14.887 --> 19:17.324
Oh, no. I love it.

19:17.457 --> 19:20.593
I want to get married
and buried in it,
but that's me.

19:21.794 --> 19:23.896
Just wondering
if all of this...

19:25.632 --> 19:26.599
If it's you.

19:28.568 --> 19:31.504
I picture you in something
more like...that.

19:32.972 --> 19:36.676
Me, too, but, this is
what the occasion calls for.

19:39.111 --> 19:41.113
When Shaun and I
decided to do this,

19:41.248 --> 19:42.982
this became more than
just our wedding.

19:44.751 --> 19:47.387
It's a chance to represent
atypical couples,

19:47.520 --> 19:50.723
to show that someone
on the spectrum

19:50.857 --> 19:52.492
can marry
a neurotypical person

19:52.625 --> 19:54.627
in the most perfect...

19:57.597 --> 20:00.633
Magical, frickin' awesome
wedding of all time.

20:02.302 --> 20:04.471
And if Shaun doesn't like it,
he'll definitely let me know.

20:07.139 --> 20:09.509
To a frickin'
awesome wedding.

20:09.642 --> 20:11.043
****

20:13.913 --> 20:16.983
DR. ANDREWS: Exposing
the renal vessels.

20:17.116 --> 20:20.019
Cerebral perfusion pressure
holding steady at 65.

20:21.788 --> 20:24.391
(BREATHES DEEPLY) Mmm.

20:24.524 --> 20:27.494
Is there anything better
than the aroma of
fresh-baked bread?

20:28.928 --> 20:31.398
Lots of things,
actually.

20:31.531 --> 20:32.865
Ligating
the feeding artery.

20:34.334 --> 20:35.935
ASHER: I try to avoid carbs.

20:36.068 --> 20:38.438
Cardiac ejection fraction
is good.

20:39.739 --> 20:41.674
How about you, Shaun?
You like your bread, right?

20:44.176 --> 20:47.179
As long as
there's no cinnamon,
nuts, seeds, or berries.

20:47.314 --> 20:49.416
Or sprouted grains.

20:49.549 --> 20:52.118
You like to be
able to choose
your own ingredients.

20:52.251 --> 20:53.920
Unless you're
sharing the bread
with someone else.

20:54.053 --> 20:56.589
Then the ingredients
should be something
you both like.

20:56.723 --> 20:58.090
Resecting away
the tumor.

20:58.224 --> 20:59.526
Unless that person
went out of their way

20:59.659 --> 21:00.893
to buy the ingredients,
in which case,

21:01.027 --> 21:02.395
the other person might be
more appreciative.

21:05.231 --> 21:07.867
You know, Jerome and I
are having a tiff, too.

21:08.000 --> 21:11.203
I suggested we wear
matching suits
to the wedding.

21:11.338 --> 21:13.239
He immediately dismissed it,
saying, "That's tacky."

21:13.373 --> 21:14.841
And I know it's tacky,

21:14.974 --> 21:18.545
but cute tacky,
not "you're trash" tacky.

21:18.678 --> 21:21.414
Maybe it's not about
suits or ingredients,

21:21.548 --> 21:24.717
but about
respecting a person
for who we are.

21:27.253 --> 21:28.455
(BLOOD GUSHES)

21:28.588 --> 21:29.689
And we got a bleeder.
It's from the renal vein.

21:29.822 --> 21:30.790
(ALARMS BEEPING)

21:30.923 --> 21:31.891
DR. LIM: CPP is dropping.

21:32.024 --> 21:33.259
ASHER:
Ejection fraction, too.

21:33.393 --> 21:34.561
DR. ANDREWS: Compressing
the renal hilum.

21:34.694 --> 21:36.729
Brain perfusion
is under 35.

21:36.863 --> 21:38.230
We need to repair
the vein.

21:38.365 --> 21:39.432
There's not enough time.

21:39.566 --> 21:40.299
We need to take
the whole kidney.

21:40.433 --> 21:42.435
****

21:44.036 --> 21:45.037
Stop!

21:45.171 --> 21:47.607
(BEEPING CONTINUES)

21:48.875 --> 21:50.410
Satinsky clamp.

21:50.543 --> 21:52.379
****

21:53.413 --> 21:55.482
Give phenylephrine
to increase CPP.

21:55.615 --> 21:58.751
Recheck T.E.E. and give fluids
to increase cardiac pre-load.

22:01.888 --> 22:03.923
Barbed suture
on the renal surface.

22:04.056 --> 22:05.792
****

22:07.460 --> 22:09.261
CPP's back up to 65.

22:10.763 --> 22:12.298
Ejection fraction's normal.

22:12.432 --> 22:14.166
****

22:18.871 --> 22:19.939
DR. ANDREWS: Myself,

22:20.072 --> 22:22.509
I'm a sucker for
an everything bagel.

22:22.642 --> 22:24.544
Detaching
the angiomyolipoma.

22:34.120 --> 22:35.287
I think Guatemala
has been good for you.

22:35.422 --> 22:36.789
Hmm. Thanks.

22:37.857 --> 22:39.325
I do, too.

22:39.459 --> 22:41.694
When you left,
you were about a two
on the hard-ass scale,

22:41.828 --> 22:43.062
and now I'd put you
at a solid five.

22:43.195 --> 22:44.831
Hmm.

22:44.964 --> 22:50.369
Which is still
a couple short of being
a successful chief.

22:50.503 --> 22:53.706
We never should have been
working on the kidneys
in the first place.

22:53.840 --> 22:54.974
No, it was
the right decision.

22:57.710 --> 22:59.378
He almost died,

22:59.512 --> 23:02.348
in exactly the way we expected
when you made the call.

23:02.482 --> 23:04.817
Audrey, I haven't
seen you in a year,
and I get this?

23:05.985 --> 23:07.820
For considering
a patient's quality of life?

23:15.862 --> 23:18.965
One of my nurses
is screwing up, badly.

23:19.098 --> 23:20.166
And if I ask you
what happened,

23:20.299 --> 23:21.734
do I lose a point
on the hard-ass scale?

23:21.868 --> 23:23.402
She's a victim of
domestic abuse.

23:24.704 --> 23:26.038
Well, that's terrible.

23:26.172 --> 23:29.942
And she almost killed
a patient because
she's...distracted.

23:30.076 --> 23:32.579
And I don't know
if she's gonna get
the help she needs.

23:32.712 --> 23:34.647
So, this is
your object lesson?

23:35.882 --> 23:37.349
(SIGHS)
To be a good chief,

23:37.484 --> 23:39.251
you have to be able
to fire battered women?

23:39.385 --> 23:42.354
When they endanger patients,
you may not have a choice.

23:46.726 --> 23:49.261
I always admired you.

23:49.395 --> 23:51.731
You know, the way
you prioritize your career,

23:51.864 --> 23:54.233
even when it came
at a cost.

23:54.366 --> 23:57.269
Choosing your job as chief
over your personal life.

23:57.403 --> 23:58.871
Now, I admired that.

24:03.375 --> 24:05.712
But I don't know
if it's Guatemala

24:05.845 --> 24:08.080
or just another
year of life,

24:08.214 --> 24:09.081
but now...

24:10.416 --> 24:13.152
I'm not sure if I do
admire your choices.

24:13.285 --> 24:14.320
Not in the same way.

24:16.188 --> 24:18.491
When I left, you were
a fantastic chief.

24:20.226 --> 24:20.960
But...

24:22.595 --> 24:24.030
I think you just could be

24:24.163 --> 24:26.132
creeping too far
up the scale.

24:26.265 --> 24:28.901
****

24:38.711 --> 24:40.246
What's all this?

24:40.379 --> 24:43.115
Huevos rancheros
con salsa verde.

24:43.249 --> 24:46.018
But you hate
huevos rancheros.

24:46.152 --> 24:48.921
It is repulsive,
but it's your favorite.

24:50.289 --> 24:51.390
Mmm!

24:53.259 --> 24:57.664
And if you're only doing
things you want to do,

24:57.797 --> 24:58.931
you're not doing enough.

25:04.003 --> 25:06.105
This is about your
wedding look, isn't it?

25:06.238 --> 25:07.774
I know it's not
your style.

25:07.907 --> 25:11.110
It's just that you would
look amazing in it.

25:11.243 --> 25:13.245
But if you want
to try something
you'd like better...

25:14.013 --> 25:15.615
Do you like your dress?

25:15.748 --> 25:17.550
It's gorgeous.

25:17.684 --> 25:21.287
Upscale Elegance
will make you happy?

25:21.420 --> 25:24.924
I think everything
is gonna look amazing.

25:25.057 --> 25:26.626
But I need you to be
okay with it.

25:30.697 --> 25:33.365
I'm okay with it.

25:33.499 --> 25:34.967
Okay.

25:35.101 --> 25:37.970
****

25:54.621 --> 25:55.888
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

25:59.425 --> 26:00.392
Hey.

26:03.696 --> 26:05.732
It's my resignation.

26:05.865 --> 26:08.534
Last night, I sat
in the parking lot
for two hours

26:08.668 --> 26:09.869
trying to call the number
you gave me.

26:13.840 --> 26:15.675
It's been an honor
working with you, Dr. Lim.

26:15.808 --> 26:18.778
****

26:24.050 --> 26:26.018
Transcortical approach
during surgery

26:26.152 --> 26:27.854
will avoid
white matter tracts

26:27.987 --> 26:29.255
and preserve Lucho's
brain function.

26:30.790 --> 26:32.024
Bit tight under the arms?

26:32.158 --> 26:34.426
No. Thank you,
it's good.

26:36.095 --> 26:37.830
Except the elbows
and thighs and calves,

26:37.964 --> 26:40.667
and the cummerbund
is restricting the blood flow
to my rectus abdominis.

26:40.800 --> 26:43.402
So, we let it out
a little bit. Vincent?

26:43.535 --> 26:45.004
Okay.
Great idea.

26:45.137 --> 26:46.939
Which I did
10 minutes ago.

26:47.073 --> 26:48.574
You didn't talk
to Lea, did you?

26:48.708 --> 26:52.144
I did.
She is very excited
about this,

26:52.278 --> 26:56.382
so I need
to make this work.

26:56.515 --> 26:57.717
Let's just size up.

26:57.850 --> 27:01.453
Well, the slim-fit cut
would look like
a-a tent-cut.

27:01.587 --> 27:03.022
Okay.

27:03.155 --> 27:05.391
Shaun, Lea would not
want you to be
tortured like this.

27:05.524 --> 27:09.395
No. I am doing this
for Lea. Okay?

27:09.528 --> 27:11.630
Sir, I-I need for you
to stand still.
Yeah.

27:11.764 --> 27:15.434
It is compressing
my external obliques.

27:15.567 --> 27:16.803
You shouldn't have to...

27:16.936 --> 27:18.671
I want to be
a good husband!
(FABRIC RIPS)

27:20.940 --> 27:22.241
Shaun, it's okay.

27:22.374 --> 27:24.343
We can just find
another tux and...
N-No!

27:25.712 --> 27:28.080
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

27:29.716 --> 27:30.917
Okay.

27:32.084 --> 27:33.385
(CELL PHONE BUZZES)

27:33.519 --> 27:36.088
****

27:36.989 --> 27:38.190
It's Lucho.

27:38.324 --> 27:41.728
****

27:41.861 --> 27:43.262
(ALARMS BEEPING)

27:43.395 --> 27:45.297
DR. LIM: He's got
a bleed in his brain.

27:45.431 --> 27:47.599
Hang frozen plasma
and clamp the drain.

27:47.734 --> 27:50.002
****

27:50.136 --> 27:51.704
(BEEPING STOPS)

27:55.574 --> 27:59.011
He has
a blood clot obstructing
his cerebral ventricle.

27:59.145 --> 28:01.280
It was our only access
to his tumor.

28:01.413 --> 28:02.181
(SIGHS)

28:03.582 --> 28:05.051
Dr. Lim was right.

28:05.184 --> 28:07.486
We should have operated on
Lucho's brain first.

28:10.189 --> 28:11.357
Yes, we should have.

28:13.893 --> 28:15.127
If we treat it with meds,

28:15.261 --> 28:17.296
we could clear the clot
in four months.

28:17.429 --> 28:18.831
The tumor will kill him
in three.

28:19.999 --> 28:22.001
****

28:23.602 --> 28:24.336
Shaun.

28:26.038 --> 28:27.206
What are you seeing?

28:27.339 --> 28:29.708
(FLATLINE)

28:29.842 --> 28:32.879
****

28:33.012 --> 28:34.680
(FLATLINE)

28:34.814 --> 28:37.817
****

28:42.688 --> 28:43.422
Nothing.

28:45.691 --> 28:47.226
Lucho is going to die.

28:47.359 --> 28:50.162
****

28:56.302 --> 28:58.170
Hable con tu mama y papa.

29:00.439 --> 29:03.375
Ellos nos encontaran
al aeropuerto.

29:04.676 --> 29:05.978
We're going home?

29:06.645 --> 29:07.746
Si.

29:08.647 --> 29:10.449
No more operations?

29:11.918 --> 29:13.185
Por ahora no.

29:15.021 --> 29:18.024
So, we'll come
back soon?

29:21.861 --> 29:23.195
No lo se.

29:25.197 --> 29:26.465
Lo siento.

29:26.598 --> 29:29.368
****

30:16.282 --> 30:18.951
Three, two, one, cheers!
ASHER: Oh!

30:19.085 --> 30:21.453
Murphy, drink up.
It's stag night,
a rite of passage.

30:23.189 --> 30:25.157
Shaun, this time tomorrow,

30:25.291 --> 30:28.861
you're gonna be
Mr. Lea Dilallo.

30:30.796 --> 30:34.100
There is no safe path
around the clot.

30:34.233 --> 30:35.968
No, there isn't.
Drink up.

30:36.102 --> 30:37.103
Drink your tequila.

30:37.904 --> 30:38.837
He's right, Shaun.

30:38.971 --> 30:41.773
(UP-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

30:41.908 --> 30:44.210
You brought Lucho here
so we could save him,

30:44.343 --> 30:46.512
and I tried to,
but I failed.

30:46.645 --> 30:49.481
And I tried to wear the suit,
and I failed at that too.

30:49.615 --> 30:51.984
And I am going to fail
as a husband.

30:52.118 --> 30:53.452
DR. PARK: Shaun, you are not.

30:53.585 --> 30:56.788
You're so open
with each other.

30:56.923 --> 30:59.225
At least you tried, Shaun.

30:59.358 --> 31:02.194
Trying doesn't matter
if it leads to failure.

31:02.328 --> 31:04.296
No. Love isn't measured
by accomplishments.

31:05.797 --> 31:06.966
It's measured by
how much you care.

31:08.334 --> 31:09.868
And what shows
you care more

31:10.002 --> 31:11.803
than trying to do
something that isn't easy?

31:13.772 --> 31:15.041
You won't always succeed,

31:15.174 --> 31:17.343
but...if you don't try,

31:19.378 --> 31:20.679
you never will.

31:20.812 --> 31:22.814
****

